The paper proposes a new approach for joint training of multiple tasks in deep reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on improving data efficiency through multitask learning with shared neural network parameters, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of 3D environments also suggests a potential connection to computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.RO, followed by cs.CV and cs.SY.
